[src:fasthttp-server/go-programming-language] Go has found widespread adoption in various domains due to its robust standard library and ease of use.
[src:fasthttp-server/go-programming-language] The interface system, and the deliberate omission of inheritance, were praised by Michele Simionato, who likened these characteristics to those of Standard ML, calling it "a shame that no popular language has followed [this] particular route".
[src:fasthttp-server/go-programming-language] By June 2015, its ranking had dropped to below 50th in the index, placing it lower than COBOL and Fortran.
[src:fasthttp-server/go-programming-language] But as of January 2017, its ranking had surged to 13th, indicating significant growth in popularity and adoption.
